@NODE CONFIG "Configuring BeepAManiac"
BeepAManiac displays the setup window if you don't already have a preference
file setup.  To config BeepAManiac use the hotkey Left-Alt-Control F10 or
use the Commodity Exchange program. @{"Setup Pic" system "display Setup.pic"}

The setup window is straight forward.  On the left is a listview that holds
all the IFF sound files.  In the middle of the window are buttons.

Directory - Opens a ASL file requester.  Select the directory where all the
sound files are located.  You can not pick sounds from different directories.
They must reside on the same directory. Path name can not be more than one
word. Eg: Ram Disk:  use RAM: instead.

About - Display the about window.

Test - A Toggle button that switchs from test mode.  Once toggled you can
single click on the listview and listen to the sound.

Hide - Save changes to ENVARC:BeepAManiac.pref and closes the window.

Quit - Abort all the changes and quit BeepAManiac.

Buffer Size - The size of the sample you want to allocate.  Note if you
don't have enough memory don't select higher size it may crash you system.
BeepAManiac handle this error.

Volume - Sets the volume for all the sounds.  This setting will over ride
the setting in the sound file. Valid setting 0 - 64.

Note: the other gadgets are disabled because they are not implemented and
may not be in future release.

Left-Alt-Control F10 for the hotkey.

@ENDNODE

@NODE DEMO "Demo"
This is a demo program only.  Only 10 sounds can used.  The first 10
sounds from the sound listview will be used.  Registered version lets you
use unlimited number of sounds.

Once you have installed BeepAManiac you can run the BeepTest which tests
BeepAManiac.  Make sure you have atleast 5 or more sounds in your selected
sound directory for it to make it worth while.

@ENDNODE

@NODE INSTALL "Installation"
If you don't have ARexx running you can't run this rexx script.  Go to
Workbench or Shell and start ARexx.  Double click on the 'Installation.rexx'
this will copy BeepAManiac to the system's WBStartup drawer.  Once installed
you can reboot your machine or double click on the BeepAManiac icon.

Manual Install
--------------
BeepAManiac can be run in Shell or Workbench.  The best method is to put it
in the WBStartup drawer which it will be automatically be executed during
startup.  The first time you run BeepAManiac, you will need to setup the
configuration. @{"Config BeepAManica  " link CONFIG}
@ENDNODE

@NODE TIPS "Tips"
To make BeepAManiac more enjoyable to listen and useful, I suggest you to
do the following:

1. Use small sample sounds.  The best is less than 8K in size.
2. Have different mix of sounds.  The more sounds the better.
3. For programmers please call DisplayBeep() when putting up an requester.
   This will give the user an indication that attention is needed.
@ENDNODE

